annotationA: RT06158p; Protein kinase activity; ATP binding; protein serine/threonine kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein phosphorylation
annotationB: Transcription factor E2f1; Transcriptional activator that binds to E2f sites. Required for wild-type growth in mitotic and polytene tissues, Contributes to the expression of replication genes at the G1-S transition and Cyclin E. Activates cell proliferation in wing imaginal disk, which requires expression of vg; Belongs to the E2F/DP family
